{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 12:19:51.900841", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nOverview of the environment\\n- Topology: 2 leaf OVS bridges (leaf_1, leaf_2), 1 spine OVS bridge (spine_1), 4 hosts (host_1_1, host_1_2, host_2_1, host_2_2).\\n- Data-plane subnet: 10.0.0.0/24 for all hosts.\\n- Management subnet: 20.0.0.0/24 for switches and controller (controller at 20.0.0.100).\\n- All switches are OpenFlow-controlled (controller target tcp:20.0.0.100:6633) with fail_mode: secure.\\n\\n1) Anomaly detection\\n- Host-to-host connectivity is fully broken, even within the same leaf:\\n  - host_1_1 -> host_1_2: Destination Host Unreachable (100% loss).\\n  - host_2_1 -> host_2_2: Destination Host Unreachable (100% loss).\\n  - host_1_1 -> host_2_1: Destination Host Unreachable (100% loss).\\n- No OpenFlow entries installed on any switch:\\n  - ovs-ofctl dump-flows on leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1 returns empty.\\n- Switch data-plane ports are up (LIVE) per OF port descriptions, and host interfaces are up with correct 10.0.0.x/24 addressing.\\n- Symptoms imply ARP/broadcast is not being forwarded (consistent with fail-mode secure and no flows).\\n\\n2) Localization of faulty component(s)\\n- Management connectivity to the controller host is good:\\n  - Pings from leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1 to 20.0.0.100 succeed with low RTT.\\n- However, all switches are disconnected from the controller at the OpenFlow control plane:\\n  - ovs-vsctl list Controller on leaf_1/leaf_2/spine_1:\\n    - is_connected: false\\n    - status: last_error=\"Connection refused\", state=BACKOFF\\n    - target: \"tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\"\\n  - netstat on switches shows no established TCP sessions to :6633.\\n- Therefore, the fault is localized to the controller service endpoint at 20.0.0.100:6633 (not the management network, not the OVS dataplane ports).\\n\\n3) Root cause analysis\\n- Root cause: The SDN controller at 20.0.0.100 is not accepting OpenFlow TCP connections on port 6633 (TCP connection refused), so switches cannot establish control sessions. With fail_mode=secure and no flows configured, the data-plane drops all traffic, including ARP, causing complete host-to-host connectivity loss.\\n- Evidence:\\n  - Controller target configured and reachable at IP level, but OVS reports connection refused and remains in BACKOFF.\\n  - Empty flow tables across all OVS switches.\\n  - Uniform host connectivity failure even within a single leaf (indicative of no L2 forwarding due to lack of controller-programmed flows).\\n\\nImpact assessment\\n- Severity: Critical. Entire fabric data-plane is down.\\n- Scope: All hosts (10.0.0.1–10.0.0.4) cannot communicate.\\n- Management plane is healthy (switches can ping the controller), isolating the issue to the controller application/service on TCP 6633 or a port mismatch.\\n\\nRelevant findings and sanity checks\\n- Hosts have correct IP configuration on 10.0.0.0/24 with link-scope routes.\\n- OVS ports to hosts and inter-switch links are UP/LIVE.\\n- Management IPs on switches: spine_1:eth2=20.0.0.1/24, leaf_1:eth3=20.0.0.2/24, leaf_2:eth3=20.0.0.3/24; all can reach 20.0.0.100.\\n- No controller-side visibility available here, but “connection refused” strongly suggests the controller process is not listening on 6633 or a different port/protocol is in use.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- Abnormal condition confirmed: complete data-plane outage.\\n- Fault localized to the SDN controller endpoint at 20.0.0.100:6633 (control plane down/refusing connections).\\n- Root cause: Controller not accepting OpenFlow sessions; switches in secure mode with no flows installed, leading to total traffic drop, including ARP., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='f3f51aaa-0736-4f20-bd2d-be860a5e310e'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
